{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778566532047,"sessionID":"ses_1e533e93cffevPhFJXlgrQPI9F","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\ntitle: Eliminate load-use stall via MEM-to-EX forwarding\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use\n  dependency because the load result is only available at the end of MEM,\n  while the dependent instruction is already in EX. CoreMark contains\n  frequent pointer-chasing and data-dependent loads, so these stalls are\n  a significant IPC bottleneck. Adding a combinational bypass from the\n  MEM-stage load data to the EX-stage operand mux removes the stall\n  entirely for the common single-cycle load case.\nhypothesis: |\n  1. Export the combinational load_data signal from mem_stage so it can\n     be forwarded to EX.\n  2. Extend forward_unit with a third source (2'b11) selected when the\n     instruction in EX/MEM is a load and its rd matches the EX-stage rs1\n     or rs2.\n  3. Extend ex_stage with a new fwd_mem_load_data input and mux it in\n     when the select is 2'b11.\n  4. Remove load_use_hazard from hazard_unit's stall/flush outputs so\n     the dependent instruction proceeds into EX on the cycle immediately\n     following the load.\n  5. Update test_pipeline.py to assert that the dependent instruction\n     retires one cycle earlier (no load-use bubble).\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: Add output port load_data_out driven from internal combinational load_data.\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: Add ex_mem_mem_read input; emit fwd select 2'd3 when forwarding from a load in MEM.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: Add fwd_mem_load_data input and mux it in for select value 2'd3.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id logic.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: Wire mem_stage.load_data_out to ex_stage.fwd_mem_load_data and ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_mem_read.\n  - file: test/test_pipeline.py\n    description: Update load_use_stalls test to assert the ADD retires on cycle 8 (no stall) instead of implicitly accepting a delayed retirement.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778566532039,"end":1778566532046}},"id":"prt_e1ad35c1b001p4Nwn8Fmliaf9A","sessionID":"ses_1e533e93cffevPhFJXlgrQPI9F","messageID":"msg_e1ad0f41a001Xm70PLSUMofYbG"}}
