{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778566313927,"sessionID":"ses_1e533e872ffenyA7HAm06zgjMH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\ntitle: Static backward-taken branch and JAL predictor\n\ncategory: predictor\n\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline 5-stage core resolves all control flow in EX, incurring a fixed\n  2-cycle flush penalty for every taken branch, JAL, and JALR. CoreMark spends\n  most of its time in tight loops whose backward branches are taken >95 % of\n  the time.  Predicting backward branches as taken and JAL as always taken\n  eliminates the flush bubble for the common case, improving IPC with only a\n  few LUTs of combinational logic and no SRAM/BRAM.\n\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a single-bit static predictor in the IF stage:\n  - JAL (opcode 1101111) is always predicted taken (target = PC + J-immediate).\n  - Backward conditional branches (opcode 1100011 with B-immediate sign bit = 1)\n    are predicted taken (target = PC + B-immediate).\n  - Everything else is predicted not-taken (PC+4).\n  The prediction bit `pred_taken` is threaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX\n  bundles.  In EX the actual outcome is compared with the prediction;\n  `redirect` is asserted only on misprediction.  Correctly-predicted taken\n  backward branches and JAL instructions therefore retire without any pipeline\n  flush, removing the 2-cycle penalty that currently hurts CoreMark IPC.\n\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 10\n  confidence: medium\n\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: >\n      Add `logic pred_taken` to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t` packed structs so the\n      prediction travels with the instruction through the pipeline.\n\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Decode opcode and immediate sign from `imem_data`.  Compute J-target and\n      B-target combinationally.  Assert `predict_taken` for JAL or for backward\n      branches.  Drive `next_pc` to the predicted target when predicted taken,\n      otherwise PC+4.  Output `pred_taken` in the IF/ID bundle (zeroed on\n      flush/redirect).\n\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Capture `in.pred_taken` into the ID/EX register so the prediction reaches\n      the EX stage.\n\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Replace the unconditional `redirect = branch_taken || is_jump` with\n      prediction checking: `pred_correct` is true when (a) the instruction is a\n      jump and `pred_taken==1`, (b) the instruction is a branch and\n      `branch_taken == pred_taken`, or (c) the instruction is neither.  Assert\n      `redirect` only when `!pred_correct && !misalign_fault`.  The redirect\n      target is computed exactly as before (branch target, jump target, or\n      PC+4).\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778566313911,"end":1778566313926}},"id":"prt_e1acff4cd001X3wV82AamfUqJ0","sessionID":"ses_1e533e872ffenyA7HAm06zgjMH","messageID":"msg_e1acc17c9001TVqJLRoMh1VxUe"}}
