{"type":"text","timestamp":1778566319819,"sessionID":"ses_1e533e872ffenyA7HAm06zgjMH","part":{"id":"prt_e1ad04871001jKIOhvNRSK1V0X","messageID":"msg_e1ad0387d001Atjpj6zieCcu5K","sessionID":"ses_1e533e872ffenyA7HAm06zgjMH","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** A static predictor in IF that predicts JAL and backward branches as taken, threads a single `pred_taken` bit through the pipeline, and only flushes on misprediction. This should eliminate the 2-cycle bubble for CoreMark's dominant loop-back branches with minimal area/Fmax impact.","time":{"start":1778566318193,"end":1778566319819}}}
